module specs.csslc.T11_W15_kwbind_and_test_attr

// § T11-W15-CSSLC : soft-keyword bindings + #[test] outer-attribute
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// § DISPATCH-ORIGIN
//   Apocky directive : "Do whatever is optimal and fully utilizes cssl and csl."
//   Wave-15 dispatch lands ≥10 GAPs from `specs/csslc/_BACKLOG.csl` so that
//   Wave-W11..W14 LoA implementations can migrate from Rust → CSSL.
//
// § GAP-AUDIT @ pre-W15
//   sweep ⟦ LoA/systems/*.csl + LoA/scenes/*.csl ⟧
//   ↦ 14-of-44 OK · 30-of-44 fail-parse
//   diagnostic-categories :
//     * "expected a pattern"        ← `let tag : T = ...` (Keyword(Tag) blocks pat)
//     * "expected an item ..."      ← `#[test]` outer-attr not-recognized
//     * "expected `)` to call args" ← bad-hex literal `0xAKA_F00...` recovery
//     * "expected an expression"    ← cascading from above
//
// § LANDED-THIS-WAVE
//
//   ── GAP-W15-A : soft-keyword binding-idents ─────────────────────────────
//
//     surface-syntax :
//       fn foo() -> u32 {
//           let tag: u32 = 42u32 ;        // ← `tag` is Keyword(Tag) — OK
//           let comptime_seed: u64 = 1 ;  // ← `comptime` is Keyword(Comptime) — OK
//           tag + comptime_seed
//       }
//       struct Foo { tag: u32, in_field: u32 }
//       let f: Foo = Foo { tag: 1u32, in_field: 2u32 } ;
//
//     pre-fix : `pat::parse_atomic_pattern` strict-required `Ident` token-kind
//       for binding-pattern. Real-world LoA uses `tag` / `ref` / `val` / `iso` /
//       etc. as struct-field-names + variable-names ; the lexer always tokenizes
//       these as their `Keyword(*)` forms, breaking pattern-parse cascade.
//
//     post-fix : new `keyword_is_soft_for_binding(Keyword) -> bool` predicate
//       in `cssl-parse/src/common.rs` ; eligible-set chosen to NOT collide with
//       expression-flavored keywords (match / loop / region / run / perform /
//       with / effect / handler — those keep their dedicated parsers).
//
//     soft-binding eligible-set :
//       Tag · Ref · Val · Box · Iso · Trn · Type · Module · Where · Comptime ·
//       In · As   ← capability-keywords + namespacy-nouns
//
//     wired into :
//       * `pat::parse_atomic_pattern`           — binding-pattern dispatch
//       * `expr::parse_let_stmt`                — mutable-binding-after-let-mut
//       * `expr::parse_const_stmt`              — const-stmt name
//       * `expr::parse_struct_constructor`      — field-init name
//       * `expr::apply_postfix Field`           — field-access RHS name
//       * `expr::parse_call_args`               — named-arg name
//       * `expr::parse_prefix soft-kw arm`      — expression-prefix-as-path
//       * `expr::looks_like_struct_body`        — struct-body peek-ahead
//       * `expr::can_start_expression`          — first-set predicate
//       * `item::parse_param_list` (via pat::)  — fn-param binding
//       * `item::parse_const_item`              — top-level const name
//       * `item::parse_struct_body`             — struct-field-decl name
//
//     codegen : zero-impact ; the only-difference is which token-kind the
//       parser slices into the `Ident.span` (Keyword vs Ident) ; downstream
//       HIR/MIR uses `source.slice(span)` for the name and is name-equivalent.
//
//     test : `tests/fixtures/soft_keyword_bindings.csl` (8-bindings · 4-fns ·
//            1-struct ; field-access + struct-constructor + let + fn-param all
//            covered)
//
//   ── GAP-W15-B : `#[name]` outer-attribute form ──────────────────────────
//
//     surface-syntax :
//       #[test]                       ← bare-name (most common)
//       #[derive(Foo, Bar)]           ← name + paren-arg-list
//       #[doc = "summary"]            ← name = expr (doc-string sugar)
//       @vertex                       ← @-form still works
//       #[test]
//       fn shader() -> i32 { ... }    ← stacked / mixed-form supported
//
//     pre-fix : `attr::parse_outer` only-recognized `@name(args)` ; `#[test]`
//       parsed as `Hash + Bracket(Square, Open) + Ident("test") + Bracket(...)`
//       and the item-dispatch failed with "expected an item" because `#` at
//       item-position has no item-form. Real-world LoA inline-tests use Rust-
//       conventional `#[test]` ; rewriting all to `@test` would be hostile to
//       Rust-fluent contributors.
//
//     post-fix : `parse_outer` now-dispatches on the leading-token :
//                  * `@`           → `parse_outer_at`     (existing path)
//                  * `# [`         → `parse_outer_hash`   (new T11-W15 path)
//                  * `# !`         → `parse_inner` (caller-driven)
//                  * else          → None (no attr at this position)
//       The two outer-paths produce identical `AttrKind::Outer` AST so HIR/
//       MIR/codegen don't need to know which surface was used.
//
//     args supported in `#[..]` form :
//       * bare         `#[test]`                     → []
//       * paren-list   `#[derive(Foo, Bar)]`         → [Positional(Foo), Positional(Bar)]
//       * eq-value     `#[doc = "summary"]`          → [Positional(Literal("summary"))]
//
//     codegen : zero-impact ; AST nodes identical to the @-form.
//
//     test : `tests/fixtures/test_attr_outer.csl` (4-fn-attrs + 1-struct-attr)
//
// § VERIFIED-RESULT
//   Pre-W15 : 14-of-44 LoA .csl pass csslc check
//   Post-W15: 21-of-44 LoA .csl pass csslc check  (+7 ; +50% improvement)
//
//   Files newly-passing : akashic.csl + economy.csl + auto_playtest.csl +
//                          alchemy.csl + content_remix.csl + crafting.csl +
//                          input_genre_fluid.csl  (all-7 hit on `#[test]`
//                          and/or `tag/ref/val` binding-name)
//
// § DEFERRED-TO-NEXT-WAVE  (specs/csslc/_BACKLOG.csl)
//
//   * GAP-W15-bad-hex-recovery : `0xAKA_T8AG_FEDCBA98u64` (intentional readable-
//     namespace-prefix hashes used in akashic / brassmarrow / city_central_hub).
//     The parser-recovery should localize the error to the literal-token rather
//     than cascade. Effort : 0.5 session (lex error-mode + parser-skip-to-
//     synchronize-token).
//
//   * GAP-W15-multi-module : `csslc build main.cssl --module-path=systems/*.csl`
//     driver loop. Effort : 1-2 sessions ; out-of-scope at parse-only
//     advancement (HIR-resolve + cgen-link-multi-source).
//
// § PRIME-DIRECTIVE
//   No harm in the making of this. Parser advancements respect sovereign-AI-
//   as-partner ; gaps were identified by reproducing real-LoA-source failure
//   paths ; fixes preserve all existing behavior bit-for-bit.
//
//   ATTESTATION : there was no hurt nor harm in the making of this, to anyone,
//   anything, or anybody.
//
// ∎ T11-W15-CSSLC-kwbind-and-test-attr
